<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>All Types of CSS Demonstration</title>

    <!-- Internal CSS -->
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            color: darkblue;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        p {
            color: #333;
            font-size: 18px;
        }

        .external-demo {
            color: green;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>

    <!-- External CSS Link -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>
    <h1>Demonstration of All Types of CSS</h1>

    <!-- Inline CSS -->
    <p style="color: red; font-size: 20px;">
        This is an example of Inline CSS.
    </p>

    <p>
        This is styled using <b>Internal CSS</b> (defined in &lt;style&gt; tag).
    </p>

    <p class="external-demo">
        This text will be styled using External CSS (from style.css file).
    </p>
</body>
</html>
external css named styele.css :
/* External CSS */
.external-demo {
    background-color: lightyellow;
    border: 2px solid green;
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 5px;
}
